title: First, use the quotient rule. You should have $$\operatorname{log_{11}}\left(6\right)-1$$.

Now, apply the change-of-base formula with $$k=5$$. You should have $$\frac{\operatorname{log_5}\left(6\right)}{\operatorname{log_5}\left(11\right)}$$. Notice, this is just $$\frac{a}{b}$$. Substitute this back into our expression.
